data.meta_description: Cory - Free download as Text File (.txt), PDF File (.pdf) or read online for free. Corazon Aquino was the first female president of the Philippines. She led the peaceful 1986 People Power Revolution that ousted the authoritarian Ferdinand Marcos from power. As president from 1986-1992, Aquino oversaw the restoration of democracy and enacted reforms like a new constitution limiting presidential power and emphasizing civil liberties. Her presidency faced challenges from coup attempts but she is remembered as an icon of Philippine democracy.
